				<baseName xml:lang="en">Optical Brightening Agent</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">增白剂</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Optical Brightener; Fluorescent Whitening Agent; OBA; FWA</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Optical Brightener; Fluorescent Whitening Agent; OBA; FWA</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Organic chemicals</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">An optical brightening agent (OBA), also known as a fluorescent whitening agent (FWA) or optical brightener, is a chemical compound that enhances the visual appearance of materials by increasing their perceived brightness and whiteness. Used in industries such as textiles, paper, detergents, and plastics, OBAs improve the look of products by absorbing ultraviolet light and re-emitting it as visible blue light, thus compensating for yellowing and making materials look whiter.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">光学增白剂（OBA），又称荧光增白剂（FWA）或光学增白剂，是一种通过提高材料的亮度和白度来改善其视觉外观的化合物。OBA 可用于纺织、造纸、洗涤剂和塑料等行业，通过吸收紫外线并将其重新发射为可见蓝光来改善产品外观，从而补偿黄变，使材料看起来更白。</common:generalComment>
